<h2 class="bac">Our Business:</h2>
<p class="bac">
Human Resources (HR) provides human resources services to our more than 285,000 employees around the world. A strategic partner with our business and corporate groups, HR provides the expertise essential for maximizing employees&#39; professional achievement and per Working together, the specialist and generalist areas provide a comprehensive service to our clients. They drive the people management aspects of the overall business strategy by delivering superior HR policy development, strategic HR advice, reward and retention programmers, management of employee relations, resourcing, diversity, learning and development and compensation and benefits.
</p>
<p class="bac">
By joining HR you will become part of a leading team of professionals and partner with an outstanding internal client base comprising leaders in their products and markets. To do this effectively you will require creativity, drive, enthusiasm and an unrelenting focus on achieving excellence.
</p>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Overview:</h2>  
<p class="bac">
As an analyst within HR, you will: 
</p>
<ul class="bac">	
	<li>Build relationships, knowledge and experience that will open doors to a wide range of future career options and opportunities </li>	
	<li>Discover unlimited opportunities to challenge yourself and grow professionally </li>	
	<li>Collaborate on exciting projects that contribute to business success and next generation advances </li>	
	<li>Work with your team to create an environment for competitive advantage and promote an internal and external reputation for excellence </li>	
	<li>Pursue meritocracy and empower every individual to maximize their potential </li>	
	<li>Connect as one HR team, share ownership and accountability for one HR agenda, and leverage HR expertise through true partnership </li>	
	<li>Understand the part that HR plays in achieving business results</li>
</ul>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Qualifications:</h2>
<ul class="bac">	
	<li>You should be commercially minded, analytical and have excellent interpersonal skills </li>	
	<li>Strong academic qualifications are important, but you&#39;ll also need to demonstrate drive, innovation and a genuine interest in the financial markets </li>	
	<li>We accept applications from a diverse range of degree disciplines such as the arts and humanities, as well as numerically focused subjects such as economics and mathematics </li>	
	<li>You&#39;ll need to be fluent in English and a second European language is also required for some roles </li>
</ul>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Training:</h2>
<p class="bac">
The best opportunity to learn about working life in Global Human Resources is to experience it first hand through our 9-week Summer Internship Programme. Aimed at students in their penultimate year, the programme runs from June to the end of August and is designed to help you decide whether our offer matches your aspirations. You&#39;ll be treated as an integral member of the team and expected to add real value. 
</p>
<p class="bac">
Fully supported by structured training, you&#39;ll also be assigned a mentor who will help you make the most of the experience. 
</p>

